The paper discusses design principles for pixel-level prediction problems, which are typically addressed in the computer vision (cs.CV) subfield. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and batch updates, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions exploring complex nonlinear predictors, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses efficient training of models, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR).
